      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "I'm not a doctor, but I can tell you that if you're still experiencing intense pain and nausea, it's probably not just gas. Appendicitis is unlikely to cause nausea, though - you'd probably be vomiting blood or showing other severe symptoms. \n\nAs for the ibuprofen, take 400-800mg every 4-6 hours as needed, but be careful not to overdo it. The maximum recommended dose is 1200mg per day. Don't take it all at once, as this can cause stomach upset. Also, be aware that if you're pregnant, you should always check with your doctor before taking any medication.",
